\b\fs48 \cf0 Prerequisites\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1060\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0 Python version must be equal to 2.7 to run Dr.seq.\
\
1. Some build-in python libraries are required:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri1060\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 1.	ConfigParser
\f1 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0 2.	subprocess\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1060\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \

\f0 2. A python package called RseQC is required for bulk-cell level QC (you can turn off bulk-cell level QC if you don\'92t want to install RseQC)\
\
3. R (>=2.1) is required to run Dr.seq.\
PDF and PNG file generation in R must be ensure. \
Some extension R libraries are required:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri1060\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 1.	cluster\
2.	fpc (you can miss this library if you don\'92t use DBSCAN as your parameter)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1060\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \

\f0 4. Alignment tools are required if you want to use the alignment function of Dr.seq (we accept STAR and bowtie2 as aligner, you can also input .sam file to skip the alignment step)\
\
5. samtools and bedtools are required\
\
6. pdflatex is required to generate QC report, otherwise you only get single QC plot in the summary/ folder. \
\
\
